<main class="container py-5">
    <div class="row d-flex align-items-stretch">
        <!-- Instructions -->
        <div class="col-lg-5 mb-4 mb-lg-0 d-flex">
            <div class="p-4 bg-light border rounded flex-fill d-flex flex-column">
                <h2 class="h4 mb-2">🛠️ What This Tool Does</h2>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Use this form to search for nearby businesses using <strong>SerpAPI</strong> and Google Maps.
                    Perfect for finding specialty shops like fly fishing stores near a location.
                </p>

                <h3 class="h5 mb-2">📋 How to Use It</h3>
                <div class="steps">
                    <div><span class="icon">🔐</span> Enter your <strong>SerpAPI key</strong> (get one at <a href="https://serpapi.com" target="_blank">serpapi.com</a>).</div>
                    <div><span class="icon">🔎</span> Choose a <strong>search term</strong> like "Fly Fishing Shops".</div>
                    <div><span class="icon">📍</span> Select a location or enter a <strong>latitude</strong> and <strong>longitude</strong> to center your search.</div>
                    <div><span class="icon">✅</span> Click <strong>Run Search</strong> to begin.</div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mb-2">ℹ️ About the Defaults</h3>
                <p class="mb-2">
                    The default search is for <strong>Fly Fishing Shops</strong> centered near <strong>Yellowstone National Park</strong>, retrieving the first <strong>100</strong>     results. You can change these to search anywhere.
                </p>

                <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                    🔒 <strong>Privacy Notice:</strong> Your API key and search inputs are never stored or logged. Everything runs securely and locally in memory.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Form -->
        <div id="formContainer" class="col-lg-7 d-flex">
            <%- include('partials/report_form.ejs') %>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>